1. `∀ i ∈ s, 0 ≤ w i`
2. `∑ i ∈ s, w i = 1`
3. `∀ i ∈ s, (s \ {i}).centerMass w x = y i`

Given that we have `z` and `c` such that `∀ i ∈ s, lineMap (y i) (x i) (c i) = z`, we can use the property of `lineMap` to express `z` as a convex combination of `x i` and `y i`.

The `lineMap` function is defined as `lineMap a b t = a + t • (b - a)`. So, `lineMap (y i) (x i) (c i) = y i + c i • (x i - y i) = (1 - c i) • y i + c i • x i`.

Since this equals `z` for all `i ∈ s`, we have `z = (1 - c i) • y i + c i • x i` for all `i ∈ s`.

